---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import SiteFooter from '../components/SiteFooter.astro';
import SiteHeader from '../components/SiteHeader.astro';
import { ci2Page, ciComponents, ciFirsts } from '../data/site';
---

<Layout title={ci2Page.title} description={ci2Page.metaDescription}>
  <div class="site-shell">
    <SiteHeader currentPath="/ci2" ctaHref="/contact" ctaLabel="Talk about CI²" />

    <main>
      <section class="relative overflow-hidden border-b border-white/[0.08]">
        <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-[radial-gradient(circle_at_top_left,rgba(200,165,106,0.16),transparent_28%),radial-gradient(circle_at_82%_18%,rgba(255,255,255,0.06),transparent_24%)]"></div>
        <div class="mx-auto grid max-w-7xl gap-10 px-6 py-18 lg:grid-cols-[1fr_0.9fr] lg:px-10 lg:py-26">
          <div class="relative z-10">
            <div class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.28em] text-brass">
              {ci2Page.heroEyebrow}
            </div>
            <h1 class="mt-6 max-w-5xl font-serif text-5xl leading-[0.93] text-paper sm:text-6xl lg:text-[5.25rem]">
              {ci2Page.heroTitle}
            </h1>
            <p class="mt-8 max-w-3xl text-lg leading-8 text-paper-dim sm:text-xl">
              {ci2Page.heroBody}
            </p>
            <div class="mt-8 max-w-2xl border-l border-brass pl-5 text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-paper-soft">
              {ci2Page.heroNote}
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="relative z-10 rounded-[2rem] border border-white/[0.08] bg-white/[0.03] p-8">
            <div class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.24em] text-brass">The formula</div>
            <div class="mt-6 font-serif text-4xl leading-tight text-paper sm:text-5xl">
              (AI²) + (HI²) = (CI²)
            </div>
            <div class="mt-8 rounded-[1.5rem] border border-white/[0.08] bg-black/20 p-6">
              <div class="flex items-center justify-center">
                <svg width="320" height="220" viewBox="0 0 320 220" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="max-w-full">
                  <line x1="46" y1="180" x2="278" y2="180" stroke="#f5f1e8" stroke-width="1" />
                  <line x1="46" y1="180" x2="46" y2="42" stroke="#f5f1e8" stroke-width="1" />
                  <line x1="46" y1="42" x2="278" y2="180" stroke="#c8a56a" stroke-width="2" />
                  <text x="30" y="118" fill="#f5f1e8" font-size="20" font-family="Georgia, serif" font-style="italic" text-anchor="end">HI</text>
                  <text x="160" y="204" fill="#f5f1e8" font-size="20" font-family="Georgia, serif" font-style="italic" text-anchor="middle">AI</text>
                  <text x="184" y="108" fill="#c8a56a" font-size="20" font-family="Georgia, serif" font-style="italic" text-anchor="middle">CI</text>
                </svg>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p class="mt-6 text-base leading-7 text-paper-dim">
              CI² is not AI and human intelligence working side by side. It is what emerges from
              the relationship between them when both are operating at full capacity.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="border-b border-white/[0.08]">
        <div class="mx-auto grid max-w-7xl gap-10 px-6 py-20 lg:grid-cols-[0.85fr_1.15fr] lg:px-10 lg:py-24">
          <div>
            <div class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.26em] text-brass">The thesis</div>
            <h2 class="mt-4 font-serif text-4xl leading-tight text-paper sm:text-5xl">
              The future isn't artificial. It's collaborative.
            </h2>
          </div>
          <div class="space-y-6 text-lg leading-8 text-paper-dim">
            <p>
              For years the story has been told in two voices. One says machines will replace us.
              The other says machines are simply tools we will learn to use. Both are incomplete.
            </p>
            <p>
              What is actually emerging is a third thing: an intelligence that exists in the space
              between artificial and human, and only when both are operating at full capacity.
            </p>
            <p>
              Anything that can be imagined can now be created. That does not make judgment,
              conceptual fluency, or taste irrelevant. It makes them more valuable.
            </p>
            <p>
              This is the realization that produced the formula. The formula became the operating
              philosophy of WORK LABS.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="bg-sand text-ink">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 py-20 lg:px-10 lg:py-24">
          <div class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.26em] text-brass-soft">The origin</div>
          <h2 class="mt-4 font-serif text-4xl leading-tight sm:text-5xl">
            How the formula was discovered.
          </h2>
          <div class="mt-8 space-y-6 text-lg leading-8 text-stone-700">
            <p>
              Cabell has spent thirty years as a conceptual artist working in the discipline of
              brand. When AI arrived, the initial fear was the one many creative people felt: the
              fear of becoming irrelevant.
            </p>
            <p>
              The discovery was the opposite. The eye trained by art movements, the instinct shaped
              by decades of conceptual practice, and the ability to hold contradiction and make
              meaning from it all became more useful in an AI era, not less.
            </p>
            <p>
              The result was not a software revelation. It was a philosophical one. The real
              leverage is not in artificial intelligence alone. It is in knowing how to direct it.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="mt-8 text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-stone-500">
            — Cabell Harris, Founder &amp; Creative Director
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="border-b border-white/[0.08]">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6 py-20 lg:px-10 lg:py-24">
          <div class="max-w-4xl">
            <div class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.26em] text-brass">The geometry</div>
            <h2 class="mt-4 font-serif text-4xl leading-tight text-paper sm:text-5xl">
              Three intelligences. One system.
            </h2>
            <p class="mt-6 max-w-3xl text-lg leading-8 text-paper-dim">
              Each component is squared. Each component matters. The third intelligence is the one
              that emerges when the first two are operating in collaboration, not opposition.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="mt-12 grid gap-5 lg:grid-cols-3">
            {ciComponents.map((item) => (
              <article class="rounded-[1.75rem] border border-white/[0.08] bg-white/[0.03] p-7">
                <div class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.22em] text-brass">{item.label}</div>
                <h3 class="mt-5 font-serif text-2xl text-paper">{item.title}</h3>
                <p class="mt-4 text-base leading-7 text-paper-dim">{item.body}</p>
              </article>
            ))}
          </div>
          <div class="mt-10 max-w-5xl rounded-[1.75rem] border border-white/[0.08] bg-black/20 p-7 text-base leading-7 text-paper-dim">
            The Pythagorean theorem says the hypotenuse squared equals the sum of the other two
            sides squared. CI² is not AI plus human intelligence standing next to each other. It
            is what emerges from the relationship between them: <strong class="text-paper">something structurally larger than either.</strong>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="border-b border-white/[0.08] bg-white/[0.02]">
        <div class="mx-auto grid max-w-7xl gap-10 px-6 py-20 lg:grid-cols-[0.85fr_1.15fr] lg:px-10 lg:py-24">
          <div>
            <div class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.26em] text-brass">The commercial argument</div>
            <h2 class="mt-4 font-serif text-4xl leading-tight text-paper sm:text-5xl">
              The scarcest resource is no longer content. It is conviction.
            </h2>
          </div>
          <div class="space-y-6 text-lg leading-8 text-paper-dim">
            <p>
              In an era when AI can generate any image, headline, or strategy deck, what becomes
              valuable is what it cannot produce alone: a genuine point of view and a company that
              knows not just what it makes, but what it means.
            </p>
            <p>
              Most organizations are unbalanced. They move fast without clarity, or think clearly
              without speed. Very few are designed to do both. That imbalance is expensive in time,
              cost, and missed opportunity.
            </p>
            <p>
              Brands and businesses built inside Collaborative Intelligence carry embedded strategic
              intelligence. The thinking is inside the brand from the beginning, not bolted on
              afterward.
            </p>
            <p>
              This is why CI² matters to Foundry, to consulting, and to the broader market position
              of WORK LABS. It is not a side service. It is the core logic underneath the business.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="bg-sand text-ink">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6 py-20 lg:px-10 lg:py-24">
          <div class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.26em] text-brass-soft">The third first</div>
          <h2 class="mt-4 font-serif text-4xl leading-tight sm:text-5xl">
            WORK LABS has been first before.
          </h2>
          <div class="mt-12 grid gap-5 lg:grid-cols-3">
            {ciFirsts.map((item) => (
              <article class="rounded-[1.75rem] border border-black/[0.08] bg-white/[0.6] p-7">
                <div class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-brass-soft">{item.year}</div>
                <h3 class="mt-5 font-serif text-3xl leading-tight">{item.title}</h3>
              </article>
            ))}
          </div>
          <div class="mt-6 text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-stone-500">
            Three firsts. Three decades apart. Each named before the industry had language for it.
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="border-b border-white/[0.08]">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 py-20 lg:px-10 lg:py-24">
          <div class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.26em] text-brass">The manifesto</div>
          <h2 class="mt-4 font-serif text-4xl leading-tight text-paper sm:text-5xl">
            A new phase of intelligence.
          </h2>
          <div class="mt-8 space-y-6 text-lg leading-8 text-paper-dim">
            <p>
              Artificial intelligence changed the game. It gave us speed, scale, memory, and
              iteration. It did not give us judgment, taste, meaning, or direction.
            </p>
            <p>
              Human intelligence was never the problem. It has always provided intuition, context,
              restraint, and clarity. On its own, it is slower, limited, and inconsistent.
            </p>
            <p class="border-l border-brass pl-5 text-paper">
              The future is not one or the other. It is the system that connects them.
            </p>
            <p>
              AI without human judgment is noise. Human judgment without AI is constraint. Together,
              they become leverage. Not incremental. Exponential.
            </p>
            <p>
              This is Collaborative Intelligence: a way of thinking, a way of working, and a way of
              building advantage. It is not about using AI because everyone can do that. It is about
              knowing where it belongs, where it does not, and how to direct it.
            </p>
            <p class="border-l border-brass pl-5 text-paper">
              Most companies do not have an AI problem. They have a thinking problem.
            </p>
            <p>
              CI² is the answer WORK LABS is building around. This is not a trend story. It is a
              transition story.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-[radial-gradient(circle_at_top,rgba(200,165,106,0.18),transparent_34%)]"></div>
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6 py-24 lg:px-10 lg:py-28">
          <div class="text-center">
            <div class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.26em] text-brass">Where this goes</div>
            <h2 class="mt-6 font-serif text-4xl leading-tight text-paper sm:text-5xl">
              Two ways CI² shows up in the world.
            </h2>
          </div>
          <div class="mt-12 grid gap-5 lg:grid-cols-2">
            <article class="rounded-[1.75rem] border border-white/[0.08] bg-white/[0.03] p-8">
              <h3 class="font-serif text-3xl text-paper">The Foundry</h3>
              <p class="mt-4 max-w-2xl text-base leading-7 text-paper-dim">
                Brands built inside Collaborative Intelligence, available as strategic platforms for
                qualified operators, acquirers, and future-minded partners.
              </p>
              <a href="/brand-foundry" class="mt-6 inline-flex text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-brass no-underline">
                Explore the Foundry
              </a>
            </article>
            <article class="rounded-[1.75rem] border border-white/[0.08] bg-white/[0.03] p-8">
              <h3 class="font-serif text-3xl text-paper">Consulting</h3>
              <p class="mt-4 max-w-2xl text-base leading-7 text-paper-dim">
                Applied CI² for companies navigating growth, repositioning, sequencing, leadership
                change, and high-consequence brand decisions.
              </p>
              <a href="/consulting" class="mt-6 inline-flex text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-brass no-underline">
                View Consulting
              </a>
            </article>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>

    <SiteFooter />
  </div>
</Layout>
